              <p align="center"><span class="txtlarge"><img src="DISTRICT_INFO/NEWS/covid_2020.2.jpg" alt="Covid_19" width="153" height="49" border="0" align="left" usemap="#Map" longdesc="DISTRICT_INFO/NEWS/COVID-19_News_Information.html"><map name="Map" id="Map"><area shape="rect" coords="2,1,167,57" href="DISTRICT_INFO/NEWS/COVID-19_News_Information.html" alt="covid19"></map></span></p>
              <p align="center"><br><br></p>
              <p align="center"><img src="images/DIVIDER/divider.jpg" width="400" height="8" alt="divider"><br></p>
              <p align="left"><span class="text14">Due to the authorization of the Oklahoma State Department Board of  Education, <strong>Holdenville School District is closed for the remainder of this year.</strong></span></p>
<p align="left" class="text14">This will include all school activities associated with the school  district until further notice. </p>
              <p align="left"><strong>March 25, 2020 COVID-19 update</strong><br>
During the State Board of Education meeting this morning, the board voted to continue the  state wide school closure of schools. Holdenville Schools will continue the Seamless Food  Program through the remainder of the school year. The time for pick up will continue from  11:00am til 12:30pm. The locations for lunch pickup are listed below.  </p>
<p align="left" class="text14">Over the next 10 days your studentâ€™s teacher or teachers will be contacting you along with  your student to help set up on-line, distance learning instruction. The instruction will become  available by April 6th. Each site will list multiple programs the district will be using and  monitoring for instruction for your child.  </p>
              <p align="center" class="text14"><em>Every site in the district is closed to everyone <br>
              except authorized personnel. </em></p>
              <p align="left" class="text14">A schedule of  authorized personnel be will listed for each site. The times will be on our Facebook site pages  and Holdenville school website along with office hours so that an appointments can be set for  pickup of information. <em>You will not be able to enter the buildings! The information will be  brought out to you as needed.</em> Holdenville Schools encourage you to work with your child to enhance their educational  learning. </p>
              <p align="left" class="text14">Once again this is a very unusual and serious situation. Each day, new information is  being released from the CDC, State Department of Health, and the State Department of  Education. </p>
              <p align="left" class="txtlarge"><span class="text14">We will continue to update our community as information is received. <br></span><br><span class="text14">Thank you for your support and understanding in these difficult times. <br><br><em>Randy Davenport, 
              Superintendent of Schools </em></span></p>
              <p align="center" class="txtlarge"><img src="images/DIVIDER/divider.jpg" alt="divider" width="400" height="8" border="0"><br></p>
              <p align="left" class="text14">                Thank you for visiting our website where our intent is to  provide timely information   for all users and a main gateway for improved communication between   parents, teachers, students  and other members of our community.<br><br>
              Our goal   and our responsibility is to help each student develop an enthusiasm for   learning, a respect for self and others, and the skills to become a   creative independent thinker and problem solver.</p>
              <p align="left" class="text14"><a href="https://ok.wengage.com/Holdenville/account/login?ReturnUrl=/Holdenville" class="TXTREUNION">MAS Wen-Gage<br>
                Student Information Center
              </a></p>
              <p class="text14">Welcome to Municipal Accounting System and Wen-Gage Student Information. Wen-Gage is a web-based software platform that helps students, teachers and parents record and track academic progress. Data analysis of such progress includes attendance, grades, transcripts and scheduling. The software system also incorporates optional teacher modules and discipline tracking.</p>
              <p class="text14">You will receive your username and password from the school secretary, as well as written instructions on how to login to the program. Once you have your username and password, you may connect by clicking theÂ <u><strong><em><a href="ok.wengage.com/holdenville">Wen-Gage Parent Portal</a></em></strong></u><a href="ok.wengage.com/holdenville">.</a></p>
